{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place olive oil, 1 tbsp of the lemon juice and salt into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>3 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Place prawns into a bowl and coat with 2 tablespoons of the marinade. Allow to marinate for 10 minutes while preparing the soup.","Add onions and garlic cloves to remaining marinade in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl using spatula.","Sauté <nobr>2 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add cucumber and chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then sauté <nobr>6 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, thread prawns and quartered lemon slices onto 6 wooden skewers and arrange them in Varoma dish (see Tips).","Add water, stock paste, pepper and remaining marinade from prawns to mixing bowl, Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and cook <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Set Varoma aside.","Add milk, flour and remaining 1 tbsp lemon juice to mixing bowl and blend <strong><nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>-9, increasing speed gradually from speed 5 to speed 9.<\/strong> Remove measuring cup, set Varoma back into position and cook <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Set Varoma aside.","Add dill to mixing bowl, season to taste and blend <strong><nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>-9, increasing speed gradually from speed 5 to speed 9,<\/strong> until frothy. Divide soup between 6 soup bowls, place a prawn skewer on top of each bowl and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["40 g olive oil","2 tbsp lemon juice","½ tsp salt","24 raw prawns, peeled and deveined","80 g brown onions, cut into halves","2 garlic cloves","500 g cucumbers, cut into pieces","1 lemon, cut into slices, each slice quartered","500 g water","1 heaped tsp Vegetable stock paste (refer to the recipe in The Basic Cookbook)","¼ tsp ground black pepper","200 g full cream milk","40 g plain flour","2 tbsp fresh dill, leaves only (optional)"]}],"id":"r156317","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-Ee2XhD9VOdc\/XZMyQM64ldI\/AAAAAAAAaig\/SMC3N2X2_TIARMX5Mhc_njLLjo-scS5aACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7xyP-cz2C___-jOs.png","title":"Cucumber soup with prawn skewers","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"12 g","fat":"9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"10 g","calories":"733 kJ \/ 175 kcal"},"usefulItems":"wooden skewers, bowl","hintsAndTricks":["If using frozen prawns, thaw before marinating.<br>- Unpeeled cucumbers add more colour and flavour to the soup.<br>- Long skewers can be cut to fit the Varoma dish.<br>- In hot weather serve this soup chilled. For a fresh summer flavour, replace dill with fresh mint or coriander.","Instead of flour use <nobr>150 g cooked<\/nobr> potatoes, cut into pieces, to thicken the soup.<br>- For a thicker soup, replace milk with pouring (whipping) cream.<br>- For a vegetarian option, replace prawns with small mushrooms <nobr>(3 cm),<\/nobr> feta cheese cubes, or tofu cubes marinated in soy sauce; and replace lemon slices with cherry tomatoes.<br>- Try adding a splash of dry white wine to the soup in the final step."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","35m","6 portions"]}